title: For Sale:  EARLY U.S. 1873 SINGLE ACTION ARMY GOOD BORE
postcontent: Here's an early Colt Model 1873 Single Action Army revolver that was manufactured in the 1870's. Chambered for the .45 Colt cartridge, this revolver has the "U.S." military property marking on the left side next to the two-line patent markings. The two-line patent marking was in use between 1873 and 1876 when another date was added and it was changed to 3-lines. The bore rates very good with strong, sharp rifling that shows only a moderate amount of light erosion. An unmarked black leather holster that is in very good condition and fits the gun well is included.
